# Weather Explorer / Weekend Trip Planner — environment
#
# This app is KEYLESS by design (NFR-COST-01, BC-PRIVACY-01). It runs with ZERO
# required environment variables. Open-Meteo (forecast + geocoding) and OSM tiles
# are free and need no API key. No database, no auth, no email, no analytics.
#
# Optional public config (safe to expose; NEXT_PUBLIC_ prefix = shipped to client):

# Override the Open-Meteo API base URLs only if self-hosting a proxy.
# Defaults are the public Open-Meteo endpoints; leave unset for normal use.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_OPEN_METEO_FORECAST_URL=https://api.open-meteo.com/v1/forecast
# NEXT_PUBLIC_OPEN_METEO_GEOCODE_URL=https://geocoding-api.open-meteo.com/v1/search

# --- Day 03, Part 2: in-app assistant (Vercel AI SDK) ---------------------------
# The ONLY keyed surface. The /api/chat route (the embedded GenUI agent) needs an
# OpenAI key; the rest of the app stays keyless. Set this in .env.local (gitignored).
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...
# OPENAI_MODEL=gpt-4o-mini   # optional; defaults to gpt-4o-mini
